SummaryEnglish: As a child Sakura Mamiya mysteriously disappeared in the woods behind her grandma's home. She returned whole and healthy, but since then she has had the power to see ghosts. Now a teenager, she just wishes the ghosts would leave her alone! At school, the desk next to Sakura's has been empty since the start of the school year, then one day her always-absent classmate shows up, and he's far more than what he seems!

1.SummaryEnglish: Sakura Mamiya is a high school student who can see spirits. Her seat in class is next to Rinne Rokudo, who for some reason, most people can see only sometimes. Sakura's friend is troubled by a series of bizarre phone calls. Sakura and Rinne investigate.

2.TitleEnglish: The Memory of the Red Ring
2.SummaryEnglish: The people at school have a dream about being approached by a woman in a kimono in a strange world with a with a red ring, imploring them to make an offering to the instrument shelter.

3.SummaryEnglish: A huge, monstrous cat attacks from the sky. To Sakura's shock, her friends Miho and Rika can see it, too.

4.TitleEnglish: If You Don't Mind Starting as Friends
4.SummaryEnglish: The son of a family of exorcists, Tsubasa Jumonji, has come to school. Right off the bat, he asks out his first love, Sakura! This bothers Rinne, but he turns a cold shoulder towards Sakura.

5.SummaryEnglish: Being broke, Rinne is overjoyed about a job Rokumon brought him: to hunt down an evil spirit for 100,000 yen. Meanwhile, something ghostly is going on at school.

6.SummaryEnglish: On her way home from school, Sakura hears the voice of a child asking from help from a roadside shrine. She wants to talk to Rinne about it, but Rinne is busy helping mummy-like Taro.

7.SummaryEnglish: Sakura spots the spirit of a boy who'd rammed his head into a lamp post be taken away by a boy with bat wings. The next morning, Rinne and Sakura receive a bizarre request letter, but Suzu and Tomoya, who'd also been called there.

8.SummaryEnglish: In an effort to rescue Reiji's living spirit, Rinne chases Masato to Hell, where right off the bat he's forced to enter illegally, as he can't pay for the admission fee.

9.TitleEnglish: The Wig's Disappointment and the Pumpkin's Temptation
9.SummaryEnglish: Rinne's school holds their school festival. Rinne works at the cafe with Sakura, when they sense something ominous. Just then, a blonde wig flies at them.

10.SummaryEnglish: Rinne has come down with an afterlife strain of the flu. A doctor arrives to treat him, but it turns out that he's a Damashigami.

11.SummaryEnglish: Sakura, Rokumon and Tsubasa infiltrate Damashigami Company. In an effort to take down the company, Rinne challenges Sabato to a duel.

12.SummaryEnglish: Rika gets 100% on a test using a mechanical pencil that makes her smarter, but an ominous aura comes from the pencil.

13.SummaryEnglish: In a daze after having seen Rinne and Ageha holding hands, Sakura accidentally wanders into the Reidou. She's surrounded by Damashigamis, but Rinne saves her at the last second.

14.SummaryEnglish: Sakura finds the spirit of an idol by the pool, but she doesn't want to bring it up with Rinne; she's still bothered by what happened between him and Ageha.

15.SummaryEnglish: Rinne tries to set things straight with Sakura about Ageha. Every time he tries to talk to her, he gets interrupted. Something odd comes out of the bento box that Ageha gives him.

16.SummaryEnglish: Tsubasa invites Sakura to visit a huge tree at the elementary school where they met, but there's something not right about the tree.

17.SummaryEnglish: Tsubasa is upset: Rinne keeps getting between him and Sakura. But Masato the devil appears before him, offering what appears to be a solution.

18.SummaryEnglish: During her pursuit of the Damashigami, Ageha encounters a Shirushigami named Kain. She goes crying to Rinne after he mocks her and her sister.

19.SummaryEnglish: Sakura and the others are trapped in a shed at Kain's home. There they find a suspicious box bearing, but they need Rinne to open it, and he's busy fighting Kain.

20.SummaryEnglish: Sakura notices something odd when she gets home: there are spirits passing through her house.

21.SummaryEnglish: It's bonus season at the Mortal Census Bureau where Kain works. Kain is tasked with delivering the money, but it gets stolen along the way.

22.SummaryEnglish: Ageha goes shopping to prepare for an intimate Christmas with Rinne, but on her way home, she notices an ominous aura coming from an abandoned house.

23.SummaryEnglish: When Tsubasa catches a cold, Rinne, Sakura, Rokumon, and Kain pay him a visit.

24.SummaryEnglish: The weather turns chilly, signalling the start of the perfect season for ramen.

25.SummaryEnglish: Sakura gets an experimental candy which can render her unable to see spirits and immediately tries it out.

1.SummaryEnglish: Ageha doesn't get along with her black cat contractor, Oboro. They fight.

2.TitleEnglish: The Sweet Tennis Court / The Letterbox
2.SummaryEnglish: A spirit is unable to pass on, held back by a desire to play tennis in the school tennis club.

3.TitleEnglish: The Disappearance of the Membership Fee
3.SummaryEnglish: Rinne's shinigami union payments go missing. Shirushigami Kain threatens him with late charges.

4.SummaryEnglish: A spirit who passed away in the Showa era returns, causing trouble all around the neighborhood.

5.TitleEnglish: Digging for Memories / Lend Me Money? / Demon at the Campsite
5.SummaryEnglish: Rinne's grandma cleans her house, and digs up some goodies. Rinne's Dad is broke again. A demon tries to take one of Sakura's friends' brothers to Hell.

6.SummaryEnglish: Rinne's homestay, Shouma, is quite a handful. Hoping to end his school assignment quickly, he goes after an evil spirit, but the spirit appears elsewhere as a living human being.

7.SummaryEnglish: Masato tricks Rinne's homestay, Shouma, into turning spirits evil. Both Rinne and Shouma are in deep trouble.

8.SummaryEnglish: A spirit is wandering around the steps of a local shrine. She'd died trying to curse Mamiya and Sakura's homeroom teacher, Suzuki-sensei.

9.TitleEnglish: Mikazukido Is the Place for the Scythe
9.SummaryEnglish: Chisame is an undefeated minibike champion. The gang wants her in the Bike Club, but she falls a bit short.

10.SummaryEnglish: Rokumon and the other black cats are invited to the celebration of a high-profile black cat before his reincarnation. Meanwhile, Rinne does battle with a hobo moth who threatens to make him even poorer.

11.TitleEnglish: A Mystery at the Summer Festival
11.SummaryEnglish: It's summer festival season. Rokudou doesn't have money to spend on such fun. Instead, he investigates rumors of "Dancing People."

12.TitleEnglish: Ghost Rubber Boat / There's Something in the Tunnel / Welcome to Nehanya!
12.SummaryEnglish: Sakura and her friends head to the beach, where they run into Rinne, Ageha, Tsubasa and Rokumon. They investigate a ghost boat, an octopus monster and a section of the beach rumored to be filled with spirits.

13.SummaryEnglish: Shima Renge is a new student at school. She has a habit of breaking people's hearts -- possibly on purpose.

14.SummaryEnglish: Shima Renge's self-imposed community service work hurts Rinne's weather box business, leaving him terrifyingly poor.

15.SummaryEnglish: Mikazukido's Recovery Cream can fix anything -- including cats. There's a spirit in the staff storage at school. The black cats go on a trip hunting for magic mushrooms.

16.SummaryEnglish: Ageha tries to break-up Rinne and Sakura with an arsenal of Shinigami tools. Renge gets involved, in an attempt to have it all blow up in Ageha's face.

17.SummaryEnglish: Demon Masato gets involved his wings stolen by a mysterious man who seems to be trying to lure Rinne into the Shinigami Elementary School reunion.

18.SummaryEnglish: Rokumon enters the Black Cat Ranking Exam in pursuit of a ranked black cat contractor discount. Kain and Ageha also have their black cat contractors join. Calamity ensues.

19.SummaryEnglish: Rokumon's plan to get the key to the Shinigami door backfires, but he gets his reward. The exam heats up even more.

20.TitleEnglish: A Pot Samurai / Demon Influenza A and Shinigami Influenza B
20.SummaryEnglish: Jumonji's expertise on hot pot ingredients may only be trumped by Rinne's intense desire to enjoy hot food on a cold day. Later, Masato deals with his cold "the demon way."

21.TitleEnglish: I'll Give You a Scarf / I'll Be Waiting on the Rink
21.SummaryEnglish: When a girl gives a scarf to a boy, a phantom scarf appears and strangles him! To lure the haunted scarf, Sakura agrees to knit a scarf for Rinne by hand.

22.SummaryEnglish: Renge does everything in her power -- and then some -- to stop her crush, Shirushigami Kain, from finding out that she's a Damashigami.

23.SummaryEnglish: Sakura picks up a scythe that becomes attached to her until she can successfully purify seven spirits.

24.SummaryEnglish: Ageha tries to put Rinne on a collar. Rinne's friend from elementary school, Matsugo, is not amused. Sakura, on the other hand, sees an opportunity.

1.SummaryEnglish: The third season of Kyoukai no Rinne.
